Amanda Khoza, News24Passport. (Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; A public prosecutor from the Ixopo Magistrate's Court has been arrested for corruption, the Hawks in KwaZulu-Natal said on Thursday.On Monday, police received information that Mduduzi Funeka, 40, had allegedly demanded money from a complainant in order for him not to be charged in a stock theft case, said Hawks spokesperson Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo.Funeka was arrested on the court premises while accepting cash in an undercover operation.He appeared in the Durban Specialised Commercial Crime Court on Tuesday and was granted R1 000 bail.The case was adjourned to January 20, 2017.Fraudulent passportIn a separate incident, police arrested a senior home affairs official, Sibonelo Biyela, 33, for fraud.Biyela was suspected of helping a foreign national obtain a fraudulent South African passport. He and his alleged accomplice, Linda Ncube, 31, were arrested at the same time. It was not clear whether Ncube was also an official at the department or not.They both appeared in the Durban Specialised Commercial Crime Court on Wednesday and were expected back in court on January 20.They were each granted R1 500 bail.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.